White Rock lake, Winfrey Point
Junior Spots A Squirrel
The wire was not in the way until the hawk suddenly stood tall and leaned forward.  I took this shot then turned to see what generated the interest.  Just in time to see a squirrel run up a tree trunk and disappear in the live oak leaves.
